BFN 

  [Text] Following inappropriate conduct by the Consular 
Section of the Canadian Embassy in Tehran toward Iranians, the 
Canadian ambassador in Iran was summoned to the Foreign Ministry 
yesterday. A protest was conveyed to him along with the 
necessary recommendations. 
  In reply, Donald P. Mcdonald, the Canadian ambassador in 
Tehran, expressed his regret, apologized for the situation, and 
promised that such conduct would be prevented. 

